about:
Hello! My name is Shrey - and I'm currently a third year Co-op student studying a Bachelor of Computer Science at UNSW!

I am also a casual academic for the university - teaching and administrating COMP1511, Programming Fundamentals. I have a passion for teaching, web-development and solving interesting problems (additionally, slightly an addict to League of Legends, and more recently - Valorant).

Outside of work and academics, I love to volunteer! Currently, I am the Co-President of CSESoc - UNSW's constituent society for computing students. I Co-lead a team of 150 volunteers to deliver events, programs and upskilling workshops for an audience of over 9500 students!
